I don't know the specifics of this test, other than it being held at the China Lake Testing Grounds, but I would assume it was to prove the effectiveness of a GPS guided munition in destroying the target and nothing else. A bomb of this size would ordinarily leave NOTHING behind, much less simply flip the vehicle.

images.description: I work at a pet store and this sweet girl got surrendered to us this morning. She wouldn't stop crying when she was in the kennel so I just let her follow me around the shop. She got adopted this afternoon by a family with 3 kids who will spoil her forever. Thought id share

In 6th grade, I had a huge crush on my mom's best friend's son. One night when our family was over at their house, my crush and I ended up watching a movie alone while sitting close to each other on the couch. What a strike of luck! 

Unfortunately, I started falling asleep as the movie played, and this newfound level of relaxation caused me to released a horrifyingly loud fart that echoed through the 2 story living room. Panicked and mortified, my damage control instinct kicked in, and I started to beatbox to disguise my fart noise.

It was most definitely a poor attempt, but I eventually thought I was in the clear since he did not react. I thought I had successfully tricked him into thinking that I had decided out of nowhere to drop an unimpressive beat. I found myself relaxing, farting, and repeating the beatboxing cycle yet again. I hopelessly beatboxed no less than 5 times throughout the course of the movie.

Nothing ever came of our relationship. RIP.

images.description: This is Michelangelo’s David one of the most famous sculptures in the world. It is a prime example of a renaissance sculpture. Notice how the sculpture isn’t depicting much movement. Just the classic contrapposto pose of having the weight on one leg creating asymmetry but still a relatively balanced and vertical sculpture.

This is Bernini’s David from the Baroque art period. Notice how this is much more of a action shot almost like some one took a photo of David mid sling. Also as notice how the position of the limbs and body create diagonals. The twist of the body creates a bit of a spiral.

This is The school of Athens by Raphael and is considered by many to be the pinnacle of the Renaissance.  Note the balance of the composition. If you drew a line down the middle there would be roughly the same amount of people on both sides. That line would also bisect the two central figures. Also you can see a lot of depth in the negative space or background. Also extra credit if you can find Michelangelo’s cameo and Raphael’s self portrait

data.title: I grew a thing from a seed

images.description: I didn’t grow this but I ate it and harvested the seed.
Avocado seed or pit I think it’s the same thing. Stick some toothpicks in the side of it and put it in a glass of water.

This is a slow process. The internet told me 4 - 6 weeks. It took me closer to 10 or 12 weeks to get this far. It only grew one root so I cut it with scissors when it got to the bottom of the glass. It started to grow some other little roots after that. Don’t get frustrated at how slow it sprouts. Several weeks to get roots and a lit longer to get a stem to grow taller then the seed.  I planted it in some dirt not long after that point.

Each face of solar cell is connected to a coil of copper wire under the opposing solar cell. When the rotor is lit from above the top solar cell provides electric current to the coil in the bottom position which becomes a temporary electromagnet that pushes against the permanent magnet in the base propelling the rotor to rotate. As the rotor turns, the coil that moves into the bottom position is likewise energized by the solar cell currently at the top- one can say the light commutates this motor. 2D magnetic levitation is provided by permanent magnets where an acrylic plate constrains the third dimension, and makes for a nice bearing surface for minimal friction.

data.title: Space Facts - Solar System Special Part 1

images.description:
The smallest rocky planet in our Solar System is that of humble Mercury. Named for the Roman God of the Messenger, this tiny world is actually smaller than many of the moons in this series.

Mercury is very similar in appearance to our Moon. Even chemically speaking, the two of them are closely related. Both are comprised of mostly metallic and silicate material. However, on Mercury the chemicals that make up the planet appear to be incredibly dense. Data we've retrieved shows that the same materials that you find on Mercury are much denser than you'd find on the Moon or even Earth.

The surface of Mercury is covered in craters. On Earth we have tectonic plates that move, grow and shrink. The plates give our planet a metaphorical facelift constantly, which is why Earth isn't just teeming with craters. We know that due to Mercury's appearance, it must not have had any geographical activity for a long time, perhaps billions of years.

Src: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mercury_%28planet%29

data.title: The school couldn't be more upset, I couldn't be more proud.
data.description:
So for the last few months my son and a handful of other boys have been bullied by this kid.  We shall call this student Pat.

Pat is a boy whose parents want him to transition into being a girl.  This poor kid has troubles man, and apparently he will be put on some kind of hormone replacement therapy this summer.

Well Pat comes to school wearing a dress some days and wearing polo and jeans on others.  He is incredibly aggressive.  On the days he dresses up like a girl he taunts mercilessly, the boys.  He has long nails and on the playground will sneak behind a group of boys and scratch them on the neck, often drawing blood.  He will also pull the boy's hair.  His response to the boys after the attacks are often along the lines of "What are you going to do, hit a girl?"  Pat has suffered almost no discipline for his anti-social behavior.

Well my son has been his number one target because my son is bigger and pretty strong.  We have had countless meetings with the administration and the last one we had was with the principle and the boy's parent's calling into it.  They didn't even have the guts to show up.  The common theme in these meetings is that we need to be tolerant of his activities and give him a wide berth.  This kid is the school's darling as he is the first and only transgendered they have had to do date.

Well I have been doing a bit of training with the boy.  We have watched some self defense videos on YouTube and every other night we hit the heavy bag for about 30 minutes.  I told the administration that if they didn't take action, I would condone the boy defending himself physically.  They were shocked that I even made mention of that.  I repeated my warning and left.

I laid out very clearly for my boy what we call our called our 'Use of Force' guidelines.  
1) If confronted physically leave the situation and look for an authority figure.
2) If you are pursued, warn him to your intention to defend yourself.
3) If he continues and lays hands on you again, beat him until you are 100% positive he can't get up.

Well today I got the call.  I drove to the school to pick him up.  When he saw me he ran to me sobbing.  I asked him if he followed the 3 rules.  He said "Yeah Daddy!", he never calls me daddy.  I wiped the tears away, told him I was proud and we walked to the truck.  The principle tried to engage me, I ignored him.  I'll deal with him and Pat's fucked up family next week.  Although I did get a call from my wife and apparently Pat got suspended too, and a doctor in the next town over is trying to rearrange his nose.

My son is downstairs watching StarWars eating an ice cream sundae while I am up here, misty eyed typing this and planning our long weekend.

Two brilliant young scientists lead the expedition. Shaw (Noomi Rapace) hopes that they will meet a race of benevolent, godlike beings who will in some way verify her religious beliefs, while Holloway (Logan Marshall-Green) is out to debunk any spiritual notions. Elysium - In the year 2159, humanity is sharply divided between two classes of people: The ultrarich live aboard a luxurious space station called Elysium, and the rest live a hardscrabble existence in Earth's ruins. His life hanging in the balance, a man named Max (Matt Damon) agrees to undertake a dangerous mission that could bring equality to the population, but Secretary Delacourt (Jodie Foster) vows to preserve the pampered lifestyle of Elysium's citizens, no matter what the cost.

Body of Lies - CIA agent Roger Ferris (Leonardo DiCaprio) hatches a bold but dangerous plan to capture terrorist Al-Saleem. With the help of Ed Hoffman (Russell Crowe) who is a master of subterfuge, Ferris creates a fake terrorist organization to prompt Al-Saleem out of hiding. At the same time, Ferris must keep his plan secret from Hani (Mark Strong), the head of Jordanian intelligence, because Ferris will lose his own life if Hani finds out.

Avatar:  The Last Airbender, interesting facts!

images.description: Avatar is an interesting franchise as is, but it gets all the stranger once you start digging and discover what was going on behind the scenes. It's a healthy obsession...

No One In Team Avatar Was Supposed To Survive Between The Last Airbender And The Legend of Korra                                                                           Isn't it sad that Aang and Sokka are the only characters who die in between the two shows? It makes sense for Aang to die since the whole concept behind becoming an Avatar involved reincarnation to some extent, but there really was no need for Sokka to die while the rest of the cast gets to survive. The thing is, the rest of the cast was supposed to die. Katara, Zuko, and Toph: none of them were going to make it to Korra but, after Sokka’s death in the show, the writers changed their mind, and there was no way to bring Sokka back. Oops.

The Series Finale Was Planned To Be Much Shorter                                                                                                               Sozin’s Comet isn't just one of Avatar’s best episodes, it's one of the best series finales ever created. It's a four-part culmination of everything Aang’s journey has been building up. Aang’s gang has finally invaded the Fire Nation, Zuko is finally confronting his family, and Aang is finally have his showdown with Fire Lord Ozai. It uses every episode to its advantage and anything less would have killed the finale. Which is exactly what could have happened.

Sozin’s Comet was always supposed to be three episodes. With three, every season would have ended with twenty episodes making each book equal as a beginning, middle, and end. Given how much the creators needed to cover, however, three just wasn't going to cut it. We're actually lucky. Usually, these stories end with the finale cramped in a designated runtime (i.e. Samurai Jack), but Avatar got one more episode to round things out.

data.title: Room painted to make it look like a cartoon
It started as a $200 aquarium from Craigslist

images.description:
This started as a 125 gallon tank with a dirty stand on Craigslist for $200. It had no hood, lights, filters or anything else. I built the top myself, added molding to the bottom and finished it with Rustoleum cabinet paint. While moving I broke the 125 gallon tank and I believe it was replaced with a 135 gallon.

The rocks are playground pebbles from Home Depot or flag stone from our creeks. The bricks came from a local construction site. It is all low budget and very stress free.

Not that it matters to anyone, but I've never measured PH or worried about temperature. I've had all kinds of animals ranging from large crayfish to a HUGE largemouth bass that was eating 24 minnows per week. 

The lights are on  a timer from 4:22pm -> 9:30pm. I see it during dinner and get to enjoy it late at night before bed. It's extremely low maintenance and has been a lot of fun.
To remain cost effective over time, I decided to make my own LED lighting system. The bulbs are extremely cheap and the light is just right.
After a few years I decided to upgrade my old dowel rod to these $5 stays.

data.title: I finally feel like I'm getting something remotely right...

images.description:
This started with a 59 cent packet of instant ramen.

My life is... It sucks. And I suck... but I decided to try to do something nice for myself. So I have decided to try to cook nicer food for myself (within my... strained financial means)

I know it may not seem like much, just instant ramen, chicken, and some veggies... but in cooking I seem to be able to momentarily escape the shittyness that consumes me day in and day out... to focus on something good and rewarding FOR ME.

It's been less than a month since I've started trying to make better food for myself and it's given me an hour or two per day where I can forget about stress, depression  anxiety, loneliness, and suicide. I am proud of how my food has been turning out, and happy about the breaks from the bad stuff ... and I wanted to share with you guys. Thank you. :]

Edit: :D
You guys liked my ramen!! Thank you so much! This totally makes my day!! I think you guys made it go on the home page as well, if so, thanks again!!

I read a couple of the funny and nice comments but not all (because I was at work) so I shall enjoy reading the rest right now!! ^-^

data.title: it got really annoying please help

images.description: So since my last one went over so well I decided to do another one.  This one is less geared towards new players and more geared towards everyone.  Here is my previous post: https://imgur.com/gallery/OzmGB

1) Learn your wedge beetle locations.  This is one of those things that a lot of players overlook, but it can really save your bacon if you take time and learn where these things are.  You can use these for any number of things. Need to get away from a charging monster? Wedge Beetle.  Need to quickly traverse a difficult area? Wedge Beetle. Want to try some fun aerial mounting techniques but lack a ledge? Wedge Beetle.  Really though, these little things will save you an absorbent amount of time and are incredibly helpful.

2) Know where to attack a monster when they're flailing on the ground or in a trap.  This is one of the two biggest things that I see among players not knowing what to do.  If a Monster is on the ground or in a trap don't just run for the head right away, especially if you want that face broken.  If your group has a hammer user let them take it instead.  Most faces are weak to blunt damage, and hammers just happen to be very blunt.  Instead if you're a blade focus on the tail, wings, or claws because this is free time to get damage in where you don't need to worry about being attacked, meaning it's also a great time to break them apart, so let everyone hit the places where they'll do the most good. So unless you're a hammer or your group doesn't have one, stay away from the face.

data.title: Tales from an ex-GameStop Employee (2005-2006 Edition)

images.description: As promised from my Blockbuster post yesterday, I’m going to talk about my brief stint at GameStop. It was my last job before I started a real ‘career’, if you wanna call it that. The timeframe was 2005 to 2006, around 1 year of employment. Might not sound like much, but it was enough to get a feel for the company.

This time it was a guy named Brandon. Like my previous boss at Blockbuster, he was incredibly easy going, fun to talk to, and turned me on to some great bands. He was a dedicated family man, too. Still is! He gave me some incredible advice before we both left the company, but I’ll get to that in a bit.

If you’re young and considering a job at GameStop, I’m not going to discourage you. But I *will* discourage you going into the job thinking you’ll be working with, and interacting with likeminded videogame enthusiasts. I had a couple really awesome co-workers at GameStop who shared my specific love for videogames, but everybody else was just there to keep the store running and take home a paycheck.

This is highly subjective, but in my case it was kind of a wakeup call. I worked in Fast Food and Rentals before my job at GameStop. At those jobs, I expected most customers to blend in with each other. I was 19 when I took this job, and I truly and naively believed that most gamers and GameStop employees would have similar interests as me. Boy was I wrong. It was pretty disheartening to see this “other” side of videogames.

data.title: Google just killed image searches, to help Getty Images

images.title: Google just killed "View Images" and about half their image search options... For Getty.

images.description:
Hello folks. Usually I don't try and make posts here but I figure you should know about this one. You may have noticed in your using of the web lately that a certain option is gone from google: "VIew Image." You know, pretty much the most useful option when you're searching for a specific image, and it's buried under eighty pages of ads on some site. Welp, it's gone! Because GettyImages bitched about it.

To quote google: 

"Today we're launching some changes on Google Images to help connect users and useful websites. 

"This will include removing the View Image button. The Visit button remains, so users can see images in the context of the webpages they're on," Google SearchLiaison tweeted on Friday. 

In other words, "You weren't giving our partner enough traffic, so we axed a very useful feature because fuck you, you're the product."

https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/after-partnering-with-getty-google-kills-view-image-button-from-search-results/articleshow/62942789.cms

Maslenitsa is the brightest, funniest and most entertaining of Russians holidays. Its history goes back to pre-Christian Russia: the main ritual of Maslenitsa is the burning of the straw figure of the Winter - an echo of pagan rituals. Today, Maslenitsa is a symbol of Russian folk festivals with a millennial history. No country in the world does celebrate something like this!

For foreign visitors, who arrive in Russia it is a lucky chance to participate the celebration of Maslenitsa, the Pancake Day. After all, it means to touch the real Russian exotica, to get on the live pages of Russian history, to witness the original traditions of the largest state in the world. Today Russia celebrates Maslenitsa the old way – huge folk festivals full of fun and games.

data.title: More tales from a security officer (Nightclub Edition)

images.description: Welcome back to another exciting episode of "what the fuck just happened and what are you doing?". As my previous tales earned me a modest couple of points (I'm now approved of) I figured they weren't as mediocre as I may have suggested. So buckle up disable the alarm system, unplug the telephone and shutdown the cctv because it's about to get rowdy.

Before I worked in static security I worked as a door supervisor (bouncer) I'm also not your typical doorman (Graduate Games Developer, Gamer, Fantasy fan, D&D, all round nerd (not forgetting the kittens!)) Because of my relatively gentle nature I was able to talk down most situations which meant Bar managers everywhere were trying to get me on their team. I settled on a lovely group of bars which literally went from one end of the spectrum to another and all three were connected by doors inside meaning all three became one. This particular tale revolves around a predatory gentlemen who was a regular (allegedly). From my perch by the DJ booth my spidey senses begin tingling me in ways I wish my EX could have tingled me, so I took a walk around to see what I could find and find I did. A lovely young lady looking absolutely terrified escaping the smoking area. I catch up and begin to ask if she's okay and her friend tells me that Regular Reginald keeps harassing her and made unwanted physical contact. Jimmies fully rustled I assured her I would handle it and I headed into the lions den. The smoking area is a very small space about 15sq feet in all directions not a fun place to be in, I assessed Reginald who was
relatively jovial, drunk, also quite physically well built and surrounded by pals. I call on the assistance of my colleagues and we lure him upstairs and out without resistance and without argument. Job done you might think? NO!, The girls were very thankful but still a bit shaken so I sorted them out with a nice VIP booth underneath a CCTV camera and within eye sight of my perch and they began to enjoy their night again until....Reginald and his pals come back onto the dance floor. I see him walk towards the girl he was 
harassing who was now at the bar buying a drink and before I step one foot of the perch. Reginald is now lying out cold on the floor, someone took exception to his return and sparked him clean out as I was the only credible witness I pulled the lad aside who punched him while his mates got him up and out the bar. I told him simply fair play mate and let him enjoy the rest of his night. Officially no one saw a thing no police involvement a hero was born that night, thank you bar batman!

It's Friday, busy night i'm on crowd control all three venues are open as one so I'm on the stairs with my trusty clickers counting the people in and out of the two bars. From this position there's also a great view of short dresses if you know what I mean, so I often had company of lads and lasses taking in the scenery. I noticed the venue was close to capacity limits so I informed the managers I would be closing the gate in 10 minutes to alleviate the issues, I also informed the the front door staff to deny entry to bar 2 while I closed the link to bar 1 meaning Bar 1 was now a singular venue for the time being, I also made customers very aware what was happening so they could quickly regroup and not get stranded during the depressurization period (reducing crowd pressure to prevent crushes, injuries and general keep the flow of people nice etc). I closed the gate and it was suddenly all hell broke loose some people saw the gate closing and panicked thinking that something serious was going on. I tried to re-assure people it was a temporary measure but it's Chinese whispers in a night club suddenly there was about 50 people on the stairs trying get me to let them pass through. I did my job however the newly caged she-beast barged her way up like a dehydrated orphan child when a U.N truck comes rolling into his town. "LET ME OUT MY FRIENDS ARE UP THERE I WANT TO BE WITH MY FRIENDS NOW!, YOU CANT LOCK ME IN HERE ITS AGAINST THE LAW YOU'RE KIDNAPPING ME..." It's just for fifte.... "IM CALLING THE POLICE!!!!", I proceed to laugh hysterically as she desperately tries to get a signal from the basement level of the bar shoving her chubby arms between the gaps in the gate swinging her phone around trying to get signal. "Miss if you go down the stairs turn left at the DJ booth and take the stairs to the street level you can get a signal there" She storms off in said direction, head doorman comes down in hysterics asking about the caged hippo and in my best Steve Irwin impression "she's a wild one that one, cage nearly gave in but she's no match for the phone jammer". Gate is reopened everyone is reunited and buys more drinks to celebrate reuniting with there long lost loved ones.

Tldr: Making token minority friends and letting them know is a shitty thing to do. 

I have DID. I have recently changed schools which puts me in a situation where I need to get to know a bunch of people in a short period of time, and since my situation is so rare, for most of these people I am the first person with multiple personalities they ever talk to. I don’t get offended easily. Go ahead and ask questions. Even the uninformed questions that could be answered by a simple google search. I don’t mind, people are curious. You can even ask the “offensive” questions that buzzfeed tells you not to ask. That is alright. Tell me it’s weird or exciting or a bit scary, I understand. 

But PLEASE stop using me to boast about your own tolerance. JESUS CHRIST am I tired of starting to getting to know someone only to realize I am their token minority friend. In less than a month I have had this happen three times. 

“Come to the movies with us! Cause you know I’m really big on being inclusive of people who are different. You can feel safe with me, I don’t discriminate. I don’t even comment on who is gay and whatnot.” I actually have no trouble finding people to hang out with, I have friends outside of school. 

Not to mention: “You know most normal people would just think you are batshit crazy, but I just find it interesting.”  

Or my favorite: “I’m really special with my openmindedness and how much I’m willing to tolerate. Most people would just shake their heads and call you a psycho, but I just think it’s cool. I think you are awesome.” 

Worst part is I have never actually been called psycho, I’ve never been excluded because of my DID, never faced discrimination that I know of, never been insulted for it. The only discrimination I feel I face is from wannabe tolerant people who try to tell me how they are different than all the others. How good of a person they are for not insulting me to my face and excluding me. 

Basically: If you feel you deserve a medal for talking to someone, please leave them alone. 

Barely anyone will see this cause it’s a terrible time to post, but if you do, feel free to PM. Vacation started yesterday and we are bored.
